text: Madhya Nepal Municipality is one of the local level of Lamjung District out of 8 local levels. It has 10 wards and according to 2011 Nepal census, 23,385 people live in here. It has 113.86 square km area. Its center is in the office of previous Karaputar Municipality. Sundarbazar Municipality is in the east, Kaski district is in the west, Kwhlosothar Rural Municipality and Besisahar Municipality are in the north and Tanahun District is in the south of Madhya Nepal Municipality. Previous Madhya Nepal Municipality (all wards), previous Karaputar Municipality (all wards) and previous Neta V.D.C. (all wards) are included in this newly made municipality. ==References== Category:Lamjung District Category:Municipalities in Gandaki Province Category:Nepal municipalities established in 2014
title: Madhya Nepal Municipality
